			<p>I&#8217;m already underway doing recommended pre-course reading. They&#8217;re tough, but just go through them as best as you can. You&#8217;ll find it challenging, especially if you&#8217;re a non-native English speaker.</p>
<p>When the course officially begins, you&#8217;ll be well on your way to start the course with the same level of dedication.</p>
<p>Before doing the readings though, familiarize yourself with the course structure. Read the left sidebar items, browse around, watch the videos and then after you exhausted that, find the recommended readings lists and plan your time to start reading them. </p>
<p>Go to the forums and introduce yourself. Here&#8217;s my thread, <a href="https://class.coursera.org/behavioralecon-002/forum/thread?thread_id=17" rel="nofollow">https://class.coursera.org/behavioralecon-002/forum/thread?thread_id=17</a></p>

