			<p>Hi Rick, sorry about that!  Do you have a Google account?  I use WordPress.  Have you watched the videos?  The three videos I first watched were 1.  Adaptation: referring to how long you could keep your thumb in hot water) i. e.  When good things happen we are &#8220;comfortable for a short time but bad things happen, we are miserable for a longer time???? 2.  Pain threshold, Severely injured people can stand pain longer (high tolerance) that mildly injured people (low tolerance).  Pain is associated with getting better.  3.  Social adaptation-evaluation of esthetics.  We all  like attractiveness, but often settle for less when we make sense of attributes (humor, and other endearing qualities of a person).</p>

